reviewText: I like the Journey DVD! They are a Great rock band.

Concert footage from Journey's 1981 Escape tour, with hits "Open Arms," "Don't Stop Believin'," "Who's Crying Now," with Steve Perry lead vocalist performing, Neal Schon guitar, vocals , Ross Valory bass,vocals, Jonathan Cain keyboards, vocals, and Steve Smith on drums, percussion. The 1983 videos "Faithfully," "Send Her My Love," "Separate Ways (Worlds Apart),"and 1986 Raised On Radio hits "Girl Can't Help it," "I'll Be Alright Without You,"and 1996 hit, "When You Love A Woman," as well as late 70's favorites. During the period 1981 to 1983, one of the best times in AOR music, and for Journey, they defined arena rock with their stage performances. You can see them again at their height in music then.
Can never go wrong with Journey!
as good as you can get...loved it
I loved it!  It met all of my expectations and then some!
